50|$|In 2003, the Israeli {{government}} {{issued a}} plan for total withdrawal from the Gaza Strip {{and part of the}} northern West Bank by late 2005. This became known as the <b>Disengagement</b> <b>Plan.</b> The Palestinian Authority welcomed this plan, but declared that until final status, it would still consider the Gaza Strip under Israeli occupation. Many Israelis opposed the plan, and tensions were very high in Israel before and after the <b>Disengagement</b> <b>Plan</b> was approved by the Israeli Knesset on 16 February 2005.|$|R
